to filter the bad breath of the wearer.&amp;nbsp; Surgical masks on the other hand are designed to stop 99% of the exhaled bacteria from the doctor, thus protecting the patient.&amp;nbsp; This is what we should be using.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>14019272</next>\n<prev>14019167</prev>\n<first>14018052</first>\n<last>14025691</last>\n<when>1298569240</when>\n<utime>02/24/11 07:40 PM</utime>\n</post>"}